characterLimitDescription: [FR] Only use a character limit when there is a good reason for limiting the number of characters users can enter.

contactSupportIfYouHaveQuestions: [FR] Contact support if you have any questions.
dataDeliveredMessage: [FR] Check your email for the submitted form response.
descriptionDescription: [FR] The description appears below the label, and before the field. It’s used to add context and instructions for the field. It’s a great place to specify formatting requirements.
didYouFindThisToolHelpful: [FR] Did you find this tool helpful? Provide feedback
fillFormClickSubmit: [FR] Fill out the form, and click submit.
formSubmissionDisabledInPreview: [FR] Form submission is disabled in preview
ifYouAreExperiencingProblems: [FR] If you are experiencing any problems with your published form, please contact support.

publishedViewLinks: [FR] View and share your published form with these links:
publishingDisablesEditingDescription: [FR] Once you publish, you cannot make changes to this form. If changes are needed after publishing, use the form file to create and publish a new form.
publishNoAuthSubTitle: [FR] You can publish and host your form with GC forms.
publishNoAuthText: To publish your form, {{signIn}} to your GC Forms account. If you do not have a GC Forms account, {{createOne}}.
publishNoAuthTitle: [FR] Sign in to publish your form
publishYourFormInstructions: [FR] You need the following items completed before you publish your form.
question: [FR] Question
saveAndRequest: [FR] Save form and request publishing ability
saveH2: [FR] Save the form file on your computer
saveH3: [FR] Upload the form file again to edit
saveP1: [FR] We don’t save your form on our website, but don’t worry, you can save the file to your computer.

saveP3: [FR] Click the save button to download your form.
saveP4: [FR] Open the form file from the GC Form Builder’s start page to pick-up where you left off.

settingsReponseHint2: [FR] In order to publish, you need to provide a response delivery destination.

shareP3: [FR] Click the save file button to download your form.
shareP4: [FR] Email the form file to your co-workers and let them know they can preview or edit it from the GC Form Builder’s start page.
